<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-53-0728 </DOCNO><TEXT>The IEA was founded in 1974 among 21 of the 24 Member Countries of theOECD. The basic aims of the IEA are: to reduce the dependence on importedoil through energy conservation, development of indigenous oil supplies,development of alternative energy sources and energy research and development:to provide an information system on the international oil market: toco-operate with other oil producing and oil consuming countries;and toprotect IEA member countries against oil supply disruptions through aseries of emergency measures. The translation process from national statisticsto an international compatible format is discussed.</TEXT></DOC>